President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Oregon due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from April 6 to April 21, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Rosalyn L. Cole has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.